title: For Sale:  SLIDE FIRE GEN 2 AR-15 BUMP STOCK
postcontent:
Excellent condition !!!
TEXT REDACTED
Thanks for looking !!!

Factory New - Generation 2 Model

Right Hand Stock

Slide Fire Solutions' ground breaking "Slide Stock" technology and ergonomic design provide the ability to Slide Fire safely, offering a new element of entertainment for recreational shooters everywhere! 

The SSAR-15 is designed for use on all AR-15 rifles equipped with a carbine style buffer tube. There are no permanent modifications necessary to install the SSAR-15.

Simply remove the factory pistol grip and replace it with the provided interface block. The SSAR-15 replaces the factory adjustable stock by simply sliding onto the buffer tube. All tools required to install the SSAR-15 are provided. 

Applying principles that have been used for over 40 years to bump fire, the SSAR-15's radical design enables the shooter to fire and AR-15 as quickly as desired without compromising their own safety or the safety of others around them. Unlike traditional bump firing. The SSAR-15 allows the shooter to properly hold their firearm and maintain complete control at all times. In addition, as a result of the forward movement required to discharge each round, the shooter naturally corrects their point-of-aim for each shot and prevents recoil from pushing the firearm's muzzle upward in an unsafe direction.

In principal the SSAR-15 functions similar to the Gatlin system. When operating a Gatlin system the shooter operates a crank in a circular motion to activate the firing mechanism. Every 1/5 rotation of the crank will discharge a round. The shooter will then continue forward another 1/5 of a rotation to fire the next round, and so on. With the SSAR-15 the shooter activates the firing mechanism by moving the upper assembly forward to discharge a round. To discharge the next round the operator must again move the upper assembly forward. As with the Gatlin system, an AR-15 equipped with the SSAR-15 will never fire automatically.

MADE IN THE USA

Right Hand Configuration

Constructed of Premium Reinforced High Strength Polymer

Compatible with Mil-Spec and Commercial Buffer Tubes

Winter Trigger Guards and some Sling Plates may not be compatible.

INCLUDES: SSAR-15, Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions and BATFE Approval Letter.

title: For Sale:  Walk with Wick the Tree Dog Encyclopedia Volume I and Volume II $100/trade
postcontent:
There are a number of things that can and are identified with the Missouri/Arkansas Ozarks. Raccoon hunting with dogs is one of them. Coon hunting has been a tradition since the beginning, and while not as popular as it once was, is still a major part of many lives.

The Tree Dog Encyclopedia by John Wick which was privately published in 1985 is probably one of the finest books on the subject of tracking and treeing dogs in print. The book starts with an in-depth description of the recognized breeds of dogs used in this sport, i.e. Black and Tan, Bluetick, English, Plott Hound, Red Bone and Treeing Walker. Mixed breeds, or that is breeds that are not officially recognized are also covered in this section of the book.

There are then chapters covering almost all areas of this sport from breeding, training, care, hunting, buying, shipping, bench shows, medical problems, dog dangers, lost dogs, tracking lost dogs, old dogs, housing and general husbandry. The entire work is infused with practical common sense and the knowledge of years of experience from the author's point of view.

Special attention should be paid to the sections of the book dealing with training. The author presents several different techniques, for different dogs and different situations. He gives very sound advice. I personally do not agree with all the methods suggested here, but each has their own way of doing things and I certainly cannot fault the validity of any of the author's statements.

There is also a very good index of terms for those that may not be familiar with the handling of these fine animals. The book is filled with very nice black and white photographs of various breeds of dogs, both hunting and bench. There is also a delightful and helpful chapter on hunting with mules, something that is becoming more and more popular.

This is a very well written book with clear and concise instructions and comments. The reader should be warned though that this is not a book on how to train the family pet. These are working dogs; actually, very expensive working dogs and the training methods and care instructions are designed for such.

And that's just the first volume, im selling both together......Trade for hunting equipment

title: For Sale:  Elmer Wall / John Armstrong Museum Grade Kentucky Flintlock Longrifle
postcontent:
Elmer Wall / John Armstrong Museum Grade Kentucky Flintlock Longrifle 

Museum grade historically accurate contemporary John Armstrong Kentucky flintlock longrifle. Fully functional. One of, if not, the finest longrifles of its type found anywhere.

Builder: Elmer N. Wall, Winchester, Kentucky, 1993. Select rare fine grade curly maple stock. Siler lock. R.E. Davis trigger. Getz barrel: 42”, .40 Cal, 1:66 twist. German silver and brass inlays. 

Collector documentation includes detailed photographic prints of the longrifle, photograph of Elmer Wall with rifle in 2002, and original hand written notes by Elmer Wall describing the rifle and his life history.

Mr. Wall, now in his 80’s, is renowned for his outstanding quality, craftsmanship and historical accuracy. This rifle is based upon Mr. Wall’s careful studies of several of John Armstrong’s Emmitsberg, Maryland, museum and private collection pieces built between 1793 and 1830.  Armstrong was one of the most notable builders of his day. Mr. Wall incorporated specific build details and designs that were unique to John Armstrong’s pieces built during the Golden Age of Kentucky flintlock longrifles. 

Mr. Wall has built over 200 longrifles in his long, storied career. Mr. Wall considers this rifle, #187, to be one of his finest pieces.

Detailed photographs of the rifle can be found at: https://www.dropbox.com/sh/4x35405raf8crsp/C9RZu2Gq-5

Long Eye Relief
See your buck, target your buck. It’s easy with Revenge’s generous eye relief and Rapid Target Acquisition eyepiece. No more searching for the visual sweet spot when the shot is on the line.

Illuminator Lens System
Quality lenses can make or break a hunt. Our Illuminator Lens System gives you the clearest image for the cleanest shot. So take a deep breath and squeeze the trigger with complete confidence. If you’re on the mark, get out your knife. When combined with Redfield’s exclusive AccuPlex, you can quickly zero and place shots right on the money, even at long range.

These scopes are built to take anything Mother Nature can dish out: driving rain, sleet, ice and snow are no match for the rugged, airtight Revenge. Nitrogen processed maintubes stay bone-dry so the elements won’t dampen your hunt.

Impact Tested Reliability
Every scope we design gets put through its paces. Our tests dish it out to make sure every scope is tough as nails, fully waterproof and ready to hunt before they ever get to you.

Accu-Ranger Reticle
As one of the first with bullet drop compensation, Redfield’s original Accu-Ranger pioneered the reticles we take for granted today. The new Accu-Ranger blends precise holdover points hunters need with a bold center that naturally leads the eye for fast shot placement at close quarters. 

The reticle comes with precise aiming points that work with most popular hunting loads. For many standard cartridges simply sight in at 200 yards with the center crosshair, and the remaining hold points are dialed in up to 500 yards. The bottom of the circle intersects the vertical crosshair at the 300-yard aim point, the dot is your hold for 400 yards, and the bottom post provides a 500-yard aiming point. For faster, magnum-caliber rifles shooting light bullets, you can sight in at 300 yards and have hold points for 400, 500, and 600 yards.

We build our Redfield riflescopes, sights, binoculars, spotting scopes and laser rangefinders to do their jobs. Day after day. Season after season. It’s what you expect for your hard earned money. title: For Sale:  AK-47 SAR-1 with optic, accessories, and extra magazines
postcontent:
This is for an SAR-1 AK-47, it comes with a Russian made Kobra holographic sight, butt stock cleaning kit, sling, and 5 steel 30 round magazines.  The furniture is all original Romanian military, solid front, laminate rear, this is completely un-messed with.

The SAR series was banned from importation in 2003, so they are rare, and hard to find now, further I had a smith re-add the bayonet lug, thread the barrel, and install correct pattern slant break, plunger, and spring, all Romanian military parts were used.

The SAR is unique as being the only correct patterned stamped Receiver AK to feature BOTH Y dimples, which makes it the most correct AK clone on the market, and also makes it ideal as a host for an NFA (full auto) conversion if you have your SOT License.  It also features a factory optics rail.

This is NOT to be confused with the garbage WASR's, this is a completely different model, and unlike the WASR's is actually good.

The Kobra sight also has not been imported in a number of years, and is even harder to find than the rifle, it also is the type which uses common AA batteries.

I have pictures, but I'm having some technical issues so I will have to text them to you if you want to see them.

Note: The manufacturer is Cugir, but that was not in the drop down menu, so I selected the importer instead.

I have a custom built Remington Model 700 That was a 350 Remington Magnum
it has been shortened to 1.8 inch. Indiana Deer Legal casing
the factory barrel has been bedded and set back to shorten the chamber.
It comes with Redding Dies that have been ground to match. 
I have brass and about 30rds of ammo that was made by C F Gunworks.
It is toped off with a leupold 3x9.
This rifle killed 3 deer at over 300yds this past season. It is amazing!!
I would like $1800 with scope or $1600 without.

This Rifle was custom built to Indiana Specs!!!!! And is referred to as a 350 JR
 This cartridge is modeled after the Remington 350 Magnum. They shorten the case
 to 1.8 inches, I took a picture so you can see the cartridge, bullet is 200grn
and clearly meets Indiana guide lines. I hope this helps with the confusion. 
Certain rifles like the .357 magnum or .44 magnum can be bought at walmart
and are perfectly legal. Indiana says you can't go below .357 magnum. This rifle can't
be bought at WalMart they have to be custom made which the price reflects
